                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/689a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 18, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4550. For Casaday from the Secretary of the Treasury. To facilitate the flow of
                    supplies to Russia, the United States Treasury has agreed to buy gold from the
                    Russian Government in advance of delivery and on this basis the Russian
                    Government has agreed to sell $30,000,000 of gold. The British Treasury
                    representative here has been informed about this. Will you please inform
                    Ambassador Winant and Mr. Harriman. [Morgenthau.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
